# StartBag — Mission Control backend → bag_recorder_node (#465).
#
# Asks the bag_recorder_node (running inside dv_pipeline_stack) to
# spawn `ros2 bag record -s mcap -a -o /tmp/ifssim_bag_active/<name>`
# and start capturing all currently-advertised topics. Writing happens
# inside the dv_pipeline_stack container, so the recorder shares the
# SHM-tuned Fast DDS context with the publishers — full-fidelity
# 10 Hz LiDAR, full camera streams, no UDP-fragmentation drops.
#
# A successful StartBag returns immediately after the recorder has
# settled (proc.poll() shows it's still running ~500 ms post-spawn).
# The bag is finalised + moved to the bind-mounted /bags/<name>/ on
# StopBag.
#
# Only ONE recording can be active at a time. Calling StartBag while
# one is already running returns ok=false with state="already_running".

# ---------------- Request ----------------
# Directory name for the bag. The recorder writes
# /tmp/ifssim_bag_active/<bag_name>/<bag_name>_0.mcap and moves the
# whole dir to /bags/<bag_name>/ on StopBag.
#
# Caller is responsible for sanitisation (mc_backend's
# bag_recorder.compose_bag_name does this). Empty rejected.
string bag_name

---
# ---------------- Response ----------------
# True if the recorder is alive ~500 ms after spawn.
bool ok

# "recording" on success, "failed" on disk-full / spawn-failure /
# already-running. Never "stopped" (that's StopBag's response).
string state

# Absolute host-side path where the bag WILL land after StopBag.
# Populated even on partial start so the operator UI can show what
# would-have-been recorded.
string bag_path

# Diagnostic on failure. Empty on success.
string error
